Abstract: 
 A simple, sensitive and rapid method using atomic absorption spectrophotometer (AAS)&nbsp;was developed for quantitative determination of Elaidic acid in vegetable oils samples. This method is based on the ability of Elaidic acid to form complex with silver ion (Ag+), which allows the attached silver to be measured, after being extracted from the resulting&nbsp;complex and calculating the Elaidic acid concentration. Elaidic acid - Ag+&nbsp;complex&nbsp;calibration curve was linear up to 4 mg/ 100ml, with a detection limit of 0.02 mg/ 100 ml. The method showed a good precision, sensitivity, and repeatability, with an average&nbsp;recovery of 97% and an acceptable relative standard deviation (RSD%= 1.42). Results of&nbsp;Elaidic acid determination in vegetable oils were found to be in agreement with those&nbsp;obtained by standard method using gas chromatography equipped with a Mass&nbsp;spectroscopy (GC-MS). 
  This version is archived in the Arab International University (AIU), repository for open access and dissemination purposes.&nbsp; the content of this paper has not been modified from the original publication&nbsp;  
  for more information, please visit the official repository of Arab International University (AIU) https://www.aiu.edu.sy&nbsp;

